Input:  s = "babad"
Output: "bab"   (or "aba")

Input:  s = "cbbd"
Output: "bb"

Idea

Generate all substrings.

Check if each substring is a palindrome.

Track the longest palindrome.

🪜 Steps

Use two loops to generate substrings.

Use a helper function to check palindrome.

Update longest substring.


Java Code (Brute Force)
public class LongestPalindromeBrute {

    public static String longestPalindrome(String s) {

        String longest = "";

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {

            for (int j = i; j < s.length(); j++) {

                String sub = s.substring(i, j + 1);

                if (isPalindrome(sub) && sub.length() > longest.length()) {
                    longest = sub;
                }
            }
        }

        return longest;
    }

    public static boolean isPalindrome(String str) {

        int left = 0;
        int right = str.length() - 1;

        while (left < right) {
            if (str.charAt(left) != str.charAt(right))
                return false;

            left++;
            right--;
        }

        return true;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        String s = "babad";

        System.out.println(longestPalindrome(s));
    }
}

Complexity
Type	Complexity
Time	O(n³)
Space	O(1)

Why?

Generate substrings → O(n²)

Check palindrome → O(n)

Optimized Approach (Expand Around Center)

For every index i:

Expand for odd palindrome (i,i)

Expand for even palindrome (i,i+1)

Track longest substring

public class LongestPalindromeOptimal {

    public static String longestPalindrome(String s) {

        if (s == null || s.length() < 1)
            return "";

        int start = 0;
        int end = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {

            int len1 = expandFromCenter(s, i, i);     // odd
            int len2 = expandFromCenter(s, i, i + 1); // even

            int len = Math.max(len1, len2);

            if (len > end - start) {

                start = i - (len - 1) / 2;
                end = i + len / 2;
            }
        }

        return s.substring(start, end + 1);
    }

    public static int expandFromCenter(String s, int left, int right) {

        while (left >= 0 && right < s.length() &&
                s.charAt(left) == s.charAt(right)) {

            left--;
            right++;
        }

        return right - left - 1;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        String s = "babad";

        System.out.println(longestPalindrome(s));
    }
}


